ge=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1104<br> <font color=#333333>(3/28/02 6:33:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1190.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  PROPOSAL: Mini-T-Rods</span><hr size=1> All this talk of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> lacking roles beyond damage dealing, got me to thinking about the utility role I find myself in most often.  Some call it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;mana bitch,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> but I find that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rods of Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are an excellent tool that provides great flexibility in groups and on raids.  Once I have sufficient healing support, I am able to greatly reduce down time for the group or raid, and compensate for a shortage of a particular class or immediate shortage of mana.<br>
<br>
Speed, and flexibility.<br>
<br>
Those seem worthwhile things to me, and no one else brings them to the table quite like I do.  It is faster and more efficient than cannibalize, and better than twitch.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Summon Rod of Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a 57th level spell as I recall, far too late to help the majority of up and coming <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Is it possible to have lower level versions of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> T-Rods</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that would be balanced for that level and still useful?<br>
<br>
Would this be a worthwhile thing?<br>
<br>
Unlike <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Focus</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> summons, these are consumed, and if they were desirable, might be worth a group slot combined with damage dealing.<br>
<br>
I have not thoroughly thought through this idea, but I did ask myself: what do <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>I</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> bring to a group that no one else can?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Senior ArchMage, Ancient Fellowship, Xev<br>
