However, as I said, I find the flexibility and speed it adds quite desirable.<br>
<br>
I cannot remember who pointed this out originally, but <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> T-Rods</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are a two way street.  Yes, it is obviously a way to give your mana to other people, but also a way to transfer mana from healers to yourself, and is fairly efficient going both ways.  I see it as a time accellerator.<br>
<br>
While on raids, the vast majority of rods I summon are generally consumed by others, in groups I am the primary beneficiary.  With some hitpoint and regen buffs and the occasional heal I can go through mana at quite a rapid rate.<br>
<br>
Another way to see it is that I borrow mana from healers and pay it back later with interest.<br>
<br>
One problem is that at lower levels, heals are less efficient, and so it does not work as well.<br>
<br>
But I am still inclined to think that giving existing mod rods another one or two charges, and possibly adding another lower level version might well help increase the groupability of mages.<br>
<br>
